# Archon Project Structure Guide

## Core Architecture
Archon is a knowledge management and AI agent platform with a microservices architecture:

- **Frontend**: [archon-ui-main/](mdc:ARCHON/archon-ui-main/) - React/TypeScript UI
- **Backend**: [python/](mdc:ARCHON/python/) - FastAPI server with MCP tools
- **Documentation**: [docs/](mdc:ARCHON/docs/) - Docusaurus documentation
- **Docker**: [docker-compose.yml](mdc:ARCHON/docker-compose.yml) - Service orchestration

## Key Entry Points
- **Main Server**: [python/src/server/main.py](mdc:ARCHON/python/src/server/main.py)
- **MCP Server**: [python/src/mcp_server/](mdc:ARCHON/python/src/mcp_server/)
- **Frontend App**: [archon-ui-main/src/App.tsx](mdc:ARCHON/archon-ui-main/src/App.tsx)
- **Configuration**: [python/.env.example](mdc:ARCHON/python/.env.example)

## Development Commands
```bash
# Backend development
cd ARCHON/python && uv run python -m src.server.main

# Frontend development  
cd ARCHON/archon-ui-main && npm run dev

# Full stack development
cd ARCHON && make dev
```

